The SROIE Dataset (Scanned Receipts OCR and Information Extraction) is one of the most widely used benchmark datasets for OCR and document information extraction tasks.
It was introduced as part of the ICDAR 2019 Robust Reading Challenge on Scanned Receipts OCR and Information Extraction.
The dataset contains approximately 1,000 real-world scanned receipt images collected from shops, restaurants, and retail stores.
These receipts vary in layout, font style, image quality, and scanning conditions, making the dataset suitable for evaluating OCR and document understanding systems.
